widgets_values:
This group generates the starting image of the video. You can customize it in any way you want, and can use any Stable Diffusion model you'd like, from any version, as long as the output of the group stays an image.

You can also turn off all these nodes and instead load an image from an external source. You will however still have to maintain the positive and negative prompts so they adequately represent the image for the AnimateDiff workflow.

This group generates SVD XT 1.1 video using the base image as input. The checkpoint can be downloaded from:
https://civitai.com/models/207992/stable-video-diffusion-svd

The last frame generated by SVD XT 1.1 will also be used to form the starting and ending images pair used by the ToonCrafter and FILM video generators.

nodes.title: Negative Prompt
widgets_values: out of frame, mutated, blurry, child, childish
Any Stable Diffusion 1.5 model and LoRas will work here.
scale_multival affects how much motion there is in the animation.

Tile ControlNet can be downloaded from:
https://huggingface.co/lllyasviel/control_v11f1e_sd15_tile

Sparse Scribble ControlNet model can be downloaded from:
https://huggingface.co/guoyww/animatediff/blob/main/v3_sd15_sparsectrl_scribble.ckpt

You can download AnimateLCM LoRa and Motion Model here:
https://huggingface.co/wangfuyun/AnimateLCM/tree/main

AnimateDiff v3 domain adapter is available here:
https://huggingface.co/guoyww/animatediff/blob/main/v3_sd15_adapter.ckpt

Set the number of frames to generate here.
25 is a good starting point as it's what SVD XT has been trained to produce. However if you only care about AnimateDiff LCM, you can increase this to 32 frames, assuming you have enough VRAM.

Set the base resolution at which the videos will be generated.
0.57 million pixels is a good starting point as it matches SVD XT 1.1, and AnimateDiff LCM can handle it as well.
This column of nodes is used to extract the last image from the generated video.

You can use the upscale model of your choice here as well. 4x-UltraSharp is a good general purpose upscaler. You can download it from here:
https://openmodeldb.info/models/4x-UltraSharp
ToonCrafter is optimized to work on images of 512x512 pixels.
